Chairman of Ovia South West local government, Comrade Destiny Enabulele, has said that Governor Godwin Obaseki and the Peoples Democratic Party would win landslide in the locality owing to developmental projects executed in the past three years. Comrade Enabulele who denied harassing political appointees said there was no presence of APC in Ovia South West. Enabulele who spoke in Iguobazuwa, headquarters of the local government, said every ward in the locality has witnessed a touch of good governance under Obaseki. He said the renovated health centres with solar powered electricity and presence of medical personnel have boosted health care delivery in Iguobazuwa and environs. The council boss said the remaining remnants in the opposition APC would soon defect to the PDP. His words, “It is a thing of surprise to see people ascribing political heavyweight to themselves in Ovia South West. I can assure you there is no APC remaining here. “My good works and the performances of Obaseki has endeared the people to the PDP. The council workers are happy. Their salaries are paid as at when due unlike in the past when they were being owed. Obaseki’s ticketing increased our revenue and it helped us at the council” 